<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf3bcbc16-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc" identifier="/us/usc/t35/s117"><num value="117">§ 117.</num><heading> Death or incapacity of inventor</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Legal representatives of deceased inventors and of those under legal incapacity may make application for patent upon compliance with the requirements and on the same terms and conditions applicable to the inventor.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf3bcbc17-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">(<ref href="/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950">July 19, 1952, ch. 950</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/66/799">66 Stat. 799</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf3bcbc18-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf3bcbc19-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 46 (R.S. 4896, amended (1) <ref href="/us/act/1899-02-28/ch227">Feb. 28, 1899, ch. 227</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/30/915">30 Stat. 915</ref>, (2) <ref href="/us/act/1903-03-03/ch1019/s3">Mar. 3, 1903, ch. 1019, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/32/1225">32 Stat. 1225</ref>, 1226, (3) <ref href="/us/act/1908-05-23/ch188">May 23, 1908, ch. 188</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/35/245">35 Stat. 245</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The language has been considerably simplified.</p>
</note>
</notes>
